<title>USA: Concentra adopts rights plan.</title>
<headline>Concentra adopts rights plan.</headline>
<dateline>BURLINGTON, Mass. 1997-04-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Concentra Corp said on Wednesday that it has adopted a shareholder rights plan to assure fair treatment of shareholders if a person or group wants to takeover the company.</p>
<p>&quot;The rights are not being distributed in response to any specific effort to acquire control of the company, and the board of directors is not aware of any such effort,&quot; chairman and chief executive officer Lawrence Rosenfeld said in a statement.  </p>
<p>Concentra said the rights plan will offer preferred stock purchase rights can be exercised when a person or group acquires 20 percent of the company's common stock or when a person or group makes a tender offer for 20 percent or more of the company's common stock.</p>
</text>
